task.summary: First go of a test for GameManager
attempt to move Movement into its own class
moved compare to GameObject. changed item to waypoint
added new maze + tool to convert int[][] mazes to lists
added comment to a test about calculation of amount of objects in the maze
many small changes all around, added TODO's beginning of cleanup of Maze classes + interface
Array based mazes have been moved into a hierarchy with abstract parent classes
done with breaking mazes up into types and correcting test
Finished Crawler + BreadthFirst and DepthFirst + 100% test on datastructures
Added a new maze with a few roads to show Depth/Breadth first crawlers
implemented equals + hashcode in the Position class
extended the position class to calculate manhattan distances between to positions
updates to the positions classes, to better inherit the x and y position, and some javaDoc updates
extended the Manhattan tests with the normal position tests
update to two of the data structures to take advantages of the equals() and compareTo() methods
improvements to the javaDoc. Simplified the "add" method in Crawler since the check was already present in the dataStructure's add method.
Added the Greedy dataStructure, and a few updates to add support for the new Greedy dataStructure
clean up of the Greedy class
Change the constructor for the gameMaster.. it now takes a maze and a dataStructure instead of a height and width of the maze
